  "faq_items": [
    {
      "q": "What color is Timberline As Ii Slate, really?",
      "a": "A confident, slightly cool dark gray. It reads close to black in shade and as a clean slate in direct sunlight. The granule blend has a faint cool undertone that keeps it from looking flat. On a Florida elevation with strong overhead light, expect the surface to brighten visibly compared to a cloudy day."
    },
    {
      "q": "Does Timberline As Ii Slate fade over time?",
      "a": "Minimally. GAF's ceramic granule coating is engineered to hold color for 25 plus years in Florida UV. Expect a barely-visible shift toward a slightly warmer tone over the first 5 years, then stability. The full warranty covers premature fading. Source: GAF product warranty card and NRCA Asphalt Shingle Manual."
    },
    {
      "q": "How does Timberline As Ii Slate look in Florida sun versus on a cloudy day?",
      "a": "In direct overhead sun it brightens to a clear charcoal with visible dimensional shadow lines. On cloudy days it reads almost black and recedes visually, which flatters most siding colors underneath. At sunset the granule blend shows its warmth."
    },
    {
      "q": "Will Timberline As Ii Slate make my house run hotter?",
      "a": "Slightly, compared to a white or light-gray roof. In Florida, a mid-dark roof adds approximately 5 to 10 degrees Fahrenheit to attic temperatures during peak summer. Proper attic ventilation and a modern radiant barrier reduce the actual cooling-load impact to less than 20 dollars per month in most homes."
    },
    {
      "q": "How does it compare to similar shingles from other brands?",
      "a": "Very similar in daylight. The gray-family SKUs across GAF, GAF, CertainTeed, IKO, and Owens Corning sit within a small tonal window. Subtle differences in granule blend (some lean cool blue, others lean warm slate) become visible only side by side. Use the Compare tab to see direct hex deltas."
    },
    {
      "q": "Is the algae warranty enough for Florida humidity?",
      "a": "Generally yes. GAF's algae-resistance package uses copper- or zinc-infused granules that inhibit the most common Florida algae strain (Gloeocapsa magma). Expect clean performance for the warranty window with normal cleaning; in heavy-shade or low-airflow installations occasional soft-wash maintenance helps. Source: NRCA Algae Discoloration field guidance."
    }
  ],
